// d1d7-unbound-ref.scrml — detector-validation fixture for D1 + D7
// (D1-MOUNT-THROW + S-UNBOUND-REF).
//
// S202 acceptance bug 2 SHAPE: for-lift/`<each>` INLINED a component and left a
// prop unsubstituted, so the per-item body referenced an identifier bound in NO
// scope -> `ReferenceError: load is not defined` thrown on first card render at
// mount. Compiled clean; `node --check` passed; caught only by a hand-run R26.
// The current compiler rejects a plainly-undeclared identifier at COMPILE time
// (E-SCOPE-001) and the inlining substitution bug is fixed, so a clean fixture
// no longer throws an unbound-ref at mount. The detector-validation test
// reproduces the HISTORICAL mount-time `ReferenceError: x is not defined` to
// PROVE D1 (mount-throw) + D7 (`/is not defined/` match) fire. The fixture
// documents the loop-body unbound-ref shape.
<program>
type Row:struct = { id: string, name: string }
<rows>: Row[] = []
<ul>
    <each in=@rows key=@.id>
        <li : @.name>
    </each>
</ul>
</program>
